      About this item

      • WHY APPLE WATCH SERIES 8 Your essential companion for a healthy life is now even more powerful. Advanced sensors provide insights to help you better understand your health. New safety features can get you help when you need it. The bright, Always-On Retina display is easy to read, even when your wrist is down.
      • EASILY CUSTOMIZABLE Available in a range of sizes and materials, with dozens of bands to choose from and watch faces with complications tailored to whatever youre into.
      • INNOVATIVE SAFETY FEATURES Crash Detection and Fall Detection can automatically connect you with emergency services in the event of a severe car crash or a hard fall. And Emergency SOS provides urgent assistance with the press of a button.
      • ADVANCED HEALTH FEATURES Temperature sensing is a breakthrough feature that provides deep insights into womens health. Keep an eye on your blood oxygen. Take an ECG anytime. Get notifications if you have an irregular rhythm. And see how much time you spent in REM, Core, or Deep sleep with Sleep Stages.
      • SIMPLY COMPATIBLE It works seamlessly with your Apple devices and services. Unlock your Mac automatically. Find your devices with a tap. Pay and send money with Apple Pay. Apple Watch requires an iPhone 8 or later with the latest iOS version.
      • INCREDIBLE DURABILITY Tougher than tough. Its crack resistant, IP6X-certified dust resistant, and swimproof with WR50 water resistance.
      • A POWERFUL FITNESS PARTNER The enhanced Workout app gives you new ways to train, and advanced metrics for more information about your workout performance. And Apple Watch comes with three months of Apple Fitness plus free.
      • APPS ON YOUR WRIST With access to tens of thousands of apps on the App Store right on your wrist, Apple Watch is the perfect personal device for whatever you love to do.
      • STAY CONNECTED Send a text, make a call, listen to music and podcasts, use Siri, and get notifications on the go. Apple Watch Series 8 (GPS) works with your iPhone or Wi-Fi to keep you connected.
      • LEGAL DISCLAIMERS This is a summary of the main product features. See below to learn more.

      Amazon Customer
      4 out of 5 stars
      Upgrade From Fitbit Versa 2
      As an owner of several Apple products (iPhone, iPad, and MacBook Air) I took advantage of the Prime Day sale on this watch at about a $100 savings. I was happy with my Fitbit Versa 2 as it is a less expensive and simple means of capturing your heart rate and steps in real time and can alert you to notifications received on your iPhone.The Apple watch is a bit more complicated and I found there is a learning curve associated with setting it up properly. It offers a great variety of watch faces that can be customized through setting the complications in the Watch app on your iPhone. By the way the term complications threw me off at first because it simply refers to the options youd like displayed on your watch face such as temperature, heart rate, moon phase and many more.One issue I was aware of before I purchased the watch is that there is no easy way to capture your steps on this watch. Fortunately You Tube is a great resource if you get stuck with something like this and I learned the third party app Pedometer ++ will resolve this issue to some extent and you can set it up as a complication as I did in the photo above. Unfortunately there seems to be a lag such that, unlike Fitbits real time steps display, it may take a few minutes for the system to catch up. I like to see my heart rate when exercising but most of the complications display it with a heart symbol that you must touch to see your current rate. Another thing I noticed is on some watch face options the steps, for example, show up in a small font that is difficult to see with older eyes whereas others, such as in my photo, are displayed as a larger font. The band that came with the watch is a little small in that I have to use the last notch on the band. So, you might consider a larger band. Ive ordered a replacement on Amazon.Lastly, while the watch comes with a charging cord, unless you have a USB C base at home, youll need to purchase one because, unlike my other devices this requires a much smaller socket on the plug base. Otherwise, I think Im going to like the watch as it integrates well with my iPhone.

        The Apple Watch Series 8 features an enhanced electrical heart sensor and ECG app, providing valuable insights into your heart health. With the Sleep app, you can establish healthy sleep routines, monitor your sleep patterns, and receive insights to improve your sleep quality. The watch also includes a mindfulness app, helping you take moments of pause and practice mindfulness in your busy day.

        The watch's battery life ensures you stay powered throughout the day. With its efficient power management, the Apple Watch Series 8 provides all-day usage on a single charge. When it's time to recharge, the watch offers fast charging capabilities, allowing you to get back in action quickly.

        In conclusion, the Apple Watch Series 8 [GPS 45mm] is a remarkable smartwatch that seamlessly integrates into your connected lifestyle. Its stunning design, larger display, advanced fitness tracking, health features, and seamless connectivity make it the ultimate companion for active individuals.         5.0 out of 5 stars First Apple Watch
        Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2023
        Style: 45mm S/M - fits 140190mm wristsSize: 45mmColor: Midnight Aluminium Case w Midnight Sport BandVerified Purchase
        The media could not be loaded.
        This is the first Apple Watch Ive owned. I had a FitBit Versa 2 before purchasing this watch and used that pretty much every day for the past 3 years. This watch is a MAJOR upgrade. I track workouts, monitor my heart-rate, send texts, even call sometimes from it. The customization options of the watch face is absolutely incredible. My current watch face shows my heart rate, the weather, and even battery top left, but there are so many different customizations to choose from. I even use Apple Pay on it almost every time I use it. Its incredibly easy to use and all of the different utilities of the watch are worth every penny. The sync between the watch and the standard iOS apps on the iPhone are seamless as well. Way better than my old Fitbit. I plan on having this watch as long as possible. BATTERY: compared to my Fitbit, the Apple Watch battery doesnt last nearly as long. However, this watch charges pretty darn quick. I put it on the charger when I shower in the morning and shower in the evening and thats enough to keep this watch charged. Overall - Id say the charge lasts around 24 hours if youre not tracking a workout and arent checking too much. When I wake up at 5:30 AM, I put the fully charged watch on, work out for about an hour, and go about my day at work. I take it off around 9 PM and by this time, Im usually anywhere from 35-45% battery. SLEEP TRACKING: Ive used sleep tracking a few times but not every night. Im just not always comfortable sleeping with a watch on. But when I have used it, Ive really liked seeing my heart rate pattern and sleep cycles. I usually get about 8 hours of sleep a night, though so tracking this was never a priority for me.

        Overall: fantastic watch and worth every cent. 10/10

I use it for monitoring heart rate because of some medical issues and have it set up to send high heart rate notifications to my husband as well. My one complaint is that I've fallen wearing it multiple times and it has never registered that I've fallen as advertised. However, that is probably better than an overly sensitive fall detection.
